Before using shared skills, read and follow:

1. `~/.ai-registry/capability-routing.md`
2. `~/.ai-registry/skills/skills.md`

Use this template when the target project should dynamically route to skills without adopting shared workflow orchestration or MCP routing.

If the agent is dispatched as a subagent, it must not select its own workflow or role. It must follow the role, task, expected outputs, acceptance criteria, and handoff instructions assigned by the primary agent. A subagent may route to skills only within its assigned role and task scope.

Local repository instructions override shared registry guidance when more specific.
If `~/.ai-registry` is unavailable, state that and continue with local instructions only.
